# ZeroOS Project Overview

ZeroOS is a lightweight operating system that boots from USB, leaves no trace on the host machine, and runs a virtual machine from an ISO image.

## Goals

- Build a bare-metal C++ kernel with a bootloader
- Create an abstract virtualization layer to spin up arbitrary VMs
- Support both ARM and x86 (32-bit and 64-bit) architectures

## Key Constraints

- This is a freestanding (no hosted stdlib) environment — never assume libc/libstdc++ are available in kernel code
- All kernel code must be position-independent or relocatable where required by the bootloader
- Memory safety is critical — there is no OS safety net beneath this code
- The OS must leave zero forensic artifacts on the host machine's storage
